PN,40710
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1772806276
OL,3,CSarah Everard vigil organiser says
OL,4,C'much more' needs doing for women to
OL,5,Cbe safe
OL,7,F"I miss the goodness of Sarah: she was
OL,8,Fthoughtful and dependable and highly
OL,9,Fprincipled," she wrote.
OL,11,FEarlier on Tuesday, Metropolitan
OL,12,FPolice Commissioner Sir Mark Rowley
OL,13,Fhailed the "extraordinary dignity in
OL,14,Fthe face of unbearable grief" shown by
OL,15,Fthe family of Ms Everard.
OL,17,FIn a statement released by the force,
OL,18,FSir Mark said: "Sarah Everard should
OL,19,Fstill be here.
OL,26,@oD@AOUqD@LO]uD@LOUvD@]O]zD@POU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G10/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1772806276
OL,3,CSarah Everard vigil organiser says
OL,4,C'much more' needs doing for women to
OL,5,Cbe safe
OL,7,F"Five years have passed since her
OL,8,Fsenseless and devastating murder.
OL,10,F"What happened to her was a profound
OL,11,Fbetrayal: of her, of her family and
OL,12,Floved ones, and of every person who
OL,13,Fplaces their trust in policing."
OL,15,FHe added the fact that she was killed
OL,16,Fby a serving police officer, Wayne
OL,17,FCouzens, was "as devastating today as
OL,18,Fit was in 2021".
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@AOUuD@`O]yD@NOUzD@OO]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G11/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40712
SC,0012
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1772806276
OL,3,CSarah Everard vigil organiser says
OL,4,C'much more' needs doing for women to
OL,5,Cbe safe
OL,7,F"It was an unthinkable abuse of power
OL,8,Fand a total violation of the values
OL,9,Fthat the Met, and policing stands for.
OL,11,F"On the day I heard what he had done,
OL,12,FI felt devastated for the immense harm
OL,13,Fhis actions caused to the trust that
OL,14,Funderpins our relationship with the
OL,15,Fcommunities we serve.
OL,17,F"What he did shook policing to its
OL,18,Fcore. It made decent, dedicated
OL,19,Fofficers and staff across the country
OL,20,Ffurious that one of our own could
OL,21,Fcommit such a monstrous crime.
OL,26,@oD@AOUsD@AOUyD@AOU
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G12/13
OL,2,W+,"-'*%/*-'"-'*%/T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BLondon NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,408,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40713
SC,0013
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F407A1772806276
OL,3,CSarah Everard vigil organiser says
OL,4,C'much more' needs doing for women to
OL,5,Cbe safe
OL,7,F"We will always be deeply sorry: for
OL,8,Fthe unimaginable harm done to Sarah,
OL,9,Ffor the trauma endured by her family `
OL,10,Fwho have shown extraordinary dignity
OL,11,Fin the face of unbearable grief ` and
OL,12,Ffor the profound damage inflicted on
OL,13,Fthe trust Londoners should be able to
OL,14,Fplace in their police service."
OL,16,FCouzens was sentenced to a whole-life
OL,17,Fprison term at the end of his trial at
OL,18,Fthe Old Bailey in September 2021,
OL,19,Fmeaning he will never be released from
OL,20,Fjail.
OL,26,@oD@AOUvD@_O]
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                G13/13
